<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-11-02T14:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-11-02T14:36:00-05:00" n="946" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d946">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13649.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Aguascalientes</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-02T13:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1914, 1 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>At midnight the Convention declared General Eulalio Gutiérrez. Governor
                            of the State of San Luis Potosí, elected Provisional President of the
                            Republic of Mexico. The Zapatistas declared themselves perfectly
                            satisfied and avowed their allegiance to the President-elect.</p>
                        <p>General Gutiérrez is elected for a period of twenty days, when the
                            Convention, with a full attendance of thirty authorized Zapata
                            delegates, will ratify his permanency as Provisional President until his
                            duly elected successor can assume office or another be named to fill out
                            the provisional term.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>